        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19995",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "One obvious solution is to change the {{autoload()}} method to suppress errors on the call to {{self::loadClass()}}, but what happens when the file does exist, and it has  a parse error or a warning that the developer should see? Such error suppression solves one problem while causing other potential problems. The complexity of dealing with PHP errors here is a bit like a waterbed... if you push down one side, the other side pops up.\n\nThe next step would be to capture the errors and make them available to the calling script (except fatal errors of course), but this may be a performance hog. We'll need some tests and benchmarks, I think.\n\nMaybe someone else has a better idea?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-19T10:00:48.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-19T10:00:48.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19998",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jacksleight",
                        "name": "jacksleight",
                        "displayName": "Jack Sleight",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "So we have four options:\n\n1. Don't check the file exists before inclusion and get errors when not found\n2. Don't check the file exists before inclusion and suppress all errors, including parse errors\n3. Don't check the file exists before inclusion but somehow catch the PHP file not found warning and suppress it, at the cost of performance\n4. Check the file exists before inclusion, at the cost of performance\n\nNone of them are ideal really. For the time being I've settled on option 4 for my workaround. Although I've got no idea on the actual performance impact of this.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jacksleight",
                        "name": "jacksleight",
                        "displayName": "Jack Sleight",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-19T10:33:39.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-19T10:33:39.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20004",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Please see [SVN r8903|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/fisheye\/changelog\/Zend_Framework\/?cs=8903] as a possible solution.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-19T13:10:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-19T13:10:45.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20005",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Of course, this solution also suppresses any such \"file not found\" warnings from user code, such as in the following:\n\n{code}\nZend_Loader::registerAutoload();\n$foo = new Foo();\n{code}\n\nIn Foo.php:\n{code}\ninclude_once 'Foo\/Exception.php';\nclass Foo\n{}\n{code}\n\nIf '{{Foo\/Exception.php}}' is not found, then the warnings generated by this user code are invisible.\n\nWe could augment the solution with an accumulation of such warnings rather than suppressing them altogether into the void. I'll commit another version that does this shortly.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-19T13:15:04.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-19T13:15:04.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20006",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Please see [SVN 8904|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/fisheye\/changelog\/Zend_Framework\/?cs=8904] for the augmented solution.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-19T13:25:27.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-19T13:25:27.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20011",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jacksleight",
                        "name": "jacksleight",
                        "displayName": "Jack Sleight",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've just run some (fairly unscientific) benchmarks on my standard application skeleton, here's the results:\n\nAverage load time in seconds based on 10 requests:\n\nUsing simple error suppression on the include_once (@): 0.3055\nChecking file exists before inclusion (Zend_Loader::isReadable()): 0.3442\nUsing the new error suppression method in incubator: 0.3086\n\nSo, there's practically no performance hit with the new method. Looks good to me.\n\nYou make a good point regarding the inclusion of other files, but I see that as less of an issue. I guess you could always change the regex in suppressFileNotFoundWarnings() to look for the file name as well, so that only errors related to that file are suppressed? Mind you, you can't parse anything to the error handler can you? So I guess it would complicated things further.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jacksleight",
                        "name": "jacksleight",
                        "displayName": "Jack Sleight",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-19T14:32:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-19T14:32:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/21416",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yoshida@zend.co.jp",
                        "name": "yoshida@zend.co.jp",
                        "displayName": "old of Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I resolved ZF-2985 today.  Please tell me if ZF-2985 causes something wrong.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yoshida@zend.co.jp",
                        "name": "yoshida@zend.co.jp",
                        "displayName": "old of Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-04-23T10:55:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-04-23T10:55:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/26565",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Resolved in trunk in r12769. However, this is a slight change in behavior, and cannot be released until the next minor release (1.8.0). ",
